  "body": "### Component\n\nCast\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nA subcommand that encodes an event/log to the generated keccak hash.\r\n\r\nAs an example, this command could be used to generate the log hash:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ cast sig-event 'Transfer(address indexed from, address indexed to, uint256 amount)'\r\n0xddf252ad1be2c89b69c2b068fc378daa952ba7f163c4a11628f55a4df523b3ef\r\n```\r\n\r\n\n\n### Additional context\n\nAt the moment, we can obtain the correct value by correctly formatting the message that needs to be keccak'ed:\r\n- remove `indexed`\r\n- remove spaces\r\n- remove argument names\r\n\r\nThis returns the correct event log:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ cast keccak 'Transfer(address,address,uint256)'\r\n0xddf252ad1be2c89b69c2b068fc378daa952ba7f163c4a11628f55a4df523b3ef\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut this doesn't because the event string was not properly formatted before hashing it:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ cast keccak 'Transfer(address indexed from, address indexed to, uint256 amount)'\r\n0x8300af306041acf9cd3c47c1d33ac4eaadc72a429dc5f6332b85e1021d2b8d03\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
